01:00:05,582 --> 01:00:08,156
- <i>Carlo?</i>
- Mason?

690
01:00:10,671 --> 01:00:13,162
Well, well, well.

691
01:00:13,257 --> 01:00:17,255
- Am I coming to see you?
- <i>Yes, soon, I hope.</i>

692
01:00:17,344 --> 01:00:20,926
But first I need you
to pack off the boys.

693
01:00:21,014 --> 01:00:23,090
- <i>Now?</i>
- Yes, I know.

694
01:00:23,183 --> 01:00:26,018
The day you never
thought would arrive has.

695
01:00:26,102 --> 01:00:28,640
<i>Now, Cordell will fax</i>
<i>the veterinary forms...</i>

696
01:00:28,730 --> 01:00:31,897
<i>directly to</i>
<i>Animal and Plant Health...</i>

697
01:00:31,983 --> 01:00:33,976
<i>but you need to get</i>
<i>the vet affidavits...</i>

698
01:00:34,069 --> 01:00:35,693
from Sardinia.

699
01:00:39,616 --> 01:00:41,158
How are they?

700
01:00:41,243 --> 01:00:43,781
<i>They are big, Mason,</i>
<i>very big.</i>

701
01:00:50,794 --> 01:00:53,665
- Say again?
- <i>Yeah, they are big, Mason.</i>

702
01:00:53,755 --> 01:00:57,622
Really big.
Maybe 270 kilos.

703
01:00:57,717 --> 01:01:00,208
Oh, wow.

704
01:01:00,303 --> 01:01:01,880
Can you hear?

705
01:01:14,233 --> 01:01:16,392
They sound fantastic.

706
01:01:26,496 --> 01:01:27,741
Super.

707
01:02:02,698 --> 01:02:07,859
The full balance of the money is payable
upon receipt of the doctor, alive.

708
01:02:07,954 --> 01:02:10,527
Of course, you won't have to
seize him yourself.

709
01:02:10,623 --> 01:02:12,531
Rather, just point him out.

710
01:02:13,375 --> 01:02:17,538
It's preferable to all concerned if
that's the extent of your involvement...

711
01:02:17,629 --> 01:02:19,289
from this point.

712
01:02:19,381 --> 01:02:23,461
I prefer to stay involved,
make sure things go right.

713
01:02:23,552 --> 01:02:25,461
Professionals will see to that.

714
01:02:27,514 --> 01:02:29,222
I am a professional.

715
01:04:52,616 --> 01:04:55,107
Did you enjoy the performance,
<i>Commendatore?</i>

716
01:04:55,202 --> 01:04:57,111
Very much.

717
01:04:57,204 --> 01:05:01,581
Allegra, this is Dr Fell,
curator of the Capponi Library.

718
01:05:01,667 --> 01:05:02,995
Signora Pazzi.

719
01:05:03,085 --> 01:05:04,994
I'm honoured.

720
01:05:05,087 --> 01:05:06,996
Are you from America,
Doctor?

721
01:05:07,089 --> 01:05:09,710
Not originally.
I've travelled there.

722
01:05:09,800 --> 01:05:12,836
I've always wanted to visit.
New England, especially.

723
01:05:12,928 --> 01:05:15,715
I've enjoyed many
excellent meals there.

724
01:05:16,932 --> 01:05:20,467
I noticed you wrapped up
in the libretto.

725
01:05:20,561 --> 01:05:22,469
Thought this might amuse you.

726
01:05:24,606 --> 01:05:27,523
Dante's first sonnet
from <i>La Vita Nuova.</i>

727
01:05:27,609 --> 01:05:29,518
It's beautiful.

728
01:05:30,778 --> 01:05:33,696
- Rinaldo, look at this.
- I can see.

729
01:05:35,283 --> 01:05:37,525
"Joyous Love seemed to me...

730
01:05:37,619 --> 01:05:40,703
the while he held
my heart in his hands...

731
01:05:40,789 --> 01:05:42,532
and in his arms...

732
01:05:42,624 --> 01:05:44,996
my lady lay asleep...

733
01:05:45,085 --> 01:05:46,994
wrapped in a veil."

734
01:05:48,004 --> 01:05:49,249
"He woke her then...

735
01:05:49,339 --> 01:05:54,131
and trembling and obedient, she ate
that burning heart out of his hand.

736
01:05:54,219 --> 01:05:56,377
Weeping, I saw him
then depart from me."

737
01:05:57,180 --> 01:06:02,387
Dr Fell, do you believe a man could
become so obsessed with a woman...

738
01:06:02,476 --> 01:06:05,050
from a single encounter?

739
01:06:05,146 --> 01:06:08,063
Could he daily feel
a stab of hunger for her...

740
01:06:08,149 --> 01:06:11,066
and find nourishment
in the very sight of her?

741
01:06:11,152 --> 01:06:13,358
I think so.

742
01:06:13,446 --> 01:06:17,859
But would she see through the bars
of his plight and ache for him?

743
01:06:17,950 --> 01:06:20,239
- Please keep that.
- I couldn't.

744
01:06:20,328 --> 01:06:21,905
I insist.

745
01:06:32,423 --> 01:06:33,586
Goodbye.

746
01:06:35,176 --> 01:06:38,093
- Let's get something to eat.
- Of course.

747
01:06:38,178 --> 01:06:40,087
Why not?

748
01:07:12,588 --> 01:07:14,580
Is that you, Doctor?

749
01:08:05,348 --> 01:08:08,349
<i>I'd like to speak with</i>
<i>Chief Inspector Rinaldo Pazzi, please.</i>

750
01:08:08,434 --> 01:08:11,638
<i>This is Agent Clarice Starling</i>
<i>from the American FBI.</i>

751
01:08:11,729 --> 01:08:13,010
<i>One moment.</i>

752
01:08:15,608 --> 01:08:18,526
- FBI.
- I'm not here.

753
01:08:23,366 --> 01:08:24,529
<i>Inspector Pazzi.</i>

754
01:08:24,618 --> 01:08:27,453
It's Agent Starling
from the FBI. How do you do?

755
01:08:27,537 --> 01:08:31,154
Actually, I was just
leaving for the day.

756
01:08:31,248 --> 01:08:33,371
- Can I call you back tomorrow?
- <i>This won't take long.</i>

757
01:08:33,459 --> 01:08:38,536
First, thank you for sending us the
security tape from the perfume store.

758
01:08:38,631 --> 01:08:42,249
<i>When I say 'you, "I mean</i>
<i>your department... Agent Benetti.</i>

759
01:08:42,343 --> 01:08:45,546
<i>Is he there?</i>
<i>Can I speak with him?</i>

760
01:08:45,638 --> 01:08:48,555
- I'm sorry. He's gone home.
- <i>That's all right.</i>

761
01:08:48,641 --> 01:08:50,883
I should tell you this
rather than him anyway.

762
01:08:50,977 --> 01:08:53,265
I'm late for
an important appointment.

763
01:08:53,354 --> 01:08:55,975
The person I'm looking for,
Inspector...

764
01:08:56,065 --> 01:08:59,066
who is indeed shown on that tape,
is Hannibal Lecter.

765
01:08:59,152 --> 01:09:00,729
Who?

766
01:09:00,820 --> 01:09:03,738
Dr Hannibal Lecter.
You've never heard of him?

767
01:09:03,823 --> 01:09:07,572
- I'm not familiar.
- <i>And the tape confirms...</i>

768
01:09:07,660 --> 01:09:10,233
that he is
or was recently in Florence.

769
01:09:11,955 --> 01:09:14,956
- Really?
- <i>He's a very dangerous man, Inspector.</i>

770
01:09:15,042 --> 01:09:18,411
He's killed 1 <i>4</i> people
that we know of.

771
01:09:18,504 --> 01:09:20,829
- I really have to go, Miss...
- <i>Starling.</i>

772
01:09:20,923 --> 01:09:22,583
<i>Just another minute.</i>

773
01:09:22,674 --> 01:09:25,592
<i>- You sure you've never heard of him?</i>
- No, I haven't.

774
01:09:25,678 --> 01:09:27,587
Because I'm confused.

775
01:09:27,680 --> 01:09:32,092
Someone there has been accessing
our private VICAP files on Dr Lecter...

776
01:09:32,184 --> 01:09:35,185
with some regularity
on your computer.

777
01:09:35,271 --> 01:09:39,185
Everybody uses
everybody's computer here.

778
01:09:39,275 --> 01:09:42,192
Maybe one of the detectives
on <i>II Mostro...</i>

779
01:09:42,278 --> 01:09:44,235
was looking at
profiles of killers...

780
01:09:44,321 --> 01:09:46,776
I'm speaking about the computer
at your home, sir.

781
01:09:48,366 --> 01:09:51,818
<i>You're trying to catch him yourself,</i>
<i>aren't you? For the reward.</i>

782
01:09:51,912 --> 01:09:54,485
I cannot warn you
strongly enough against that.

783
01:09:54,581 --> 01:09:57,451
He killed three policemen
down in Memphis while in custody...

784
01:09:57,542 --> 01:10:01,243
<i>tearing the face off one of them,</i>
<i>and he will kill you too.</i>

785
01:10:36,039 --> 01:10:39,408
<i>- I want him out of Tuscany fast.</i>
- Believe me...

786
01:10:39,500 --> 01:10:42,455
he'll be gone
from the face of the earth fast.

787
01:10:42,545 --> 01:10:44,123
Feet-first.

788
01:11:03,941 --> 01:11:07,476
<i>Because of his avarice and his betrayal</i>
<i>of the emperor's trust...</i>

789
01:11:07,570 --> 01:11:11,817
<i>Pier della Vigna was disgraced,</i>
<i>blinded and imprisoned.</i>

790
01:11:11,907 --> 01:11:17,494
<i>Dante's pilgrim finds Pier della Vigna</i>
<i>on the seventh level of the Inferno...</i>

791
01:11:17,580 --> 01:11:21,031
<i>and, likeJudas Iscariot,</i>
<i>he died by hanging.</i>

792
01:11:21,125 --> 01:11:23,960
So judas and Pier della Vigna
are linked in Dante...

793
01:11:24,045 --> 01:11:26,370
by the avarice
he saw in them.

794
01:11:26,464 --> 01:11:30,793
In fact, avarice and hanging
are linked in the medieval mind.

795
01:11:30,885 --> 01:11:34,254
This is the earliest known
depiction of the Crucifixion...

796
01:11:34,347 --> 01:11:38,641
carved on an ivory box in Gaul
about A.D. <i>4</i>00.

797
01:11:38,726 --> 01:11:43,553
It includes the death
by hanging of judas...

798
01:11:43,647 --> 01:11:45,556
his face upturned
to the branch that suspends him.

799
01:11:45,649 --> 01:11:48,603
Here he is again on the doors
of the Benevento Cathedral...

800
01:11:48,694 --> 01:11:52,561
this time
with his bowels falling out.

801
01:11:59,705 --> 01:12:03,038
<i>It wasn't easy, but I got this number</i>
<i>without tellin'them why...</i>

802
01:12:03,125 --> 01:12:05,497
- Sorry.
- Not at all. Welcome.

803
01:12:05,586 --> 01:12:08,919
- Please join us.
- Thank you.

804
01:12:09,006 --> 01:12:11,924
On this plate from the
15th-century edition of the <i>Inferno...</i>

805
01:12:12,009 --> 01:12:15,508
Pier della Vigna's body
hangs from a bleeding tree.

806
01:12:15,596 --> 01:12:18,513
I will not belabour the obvious
parallel with judas Iscariot...

807
01:12:18,598 --> 01:12:21,516
but Dante Alighieri
needed no drawn illustration.

808
01:12:21,601 --> 01:12:26,180
It was his genius to make
Pier della Vigna, now in hell...

809
01:12:26,273 --> 01:12:29,190
speak in strained hisses
and coughing sibilants...

810
01:12:29,276 --> 01:12:32,146
as though
he is hanging still.

811
01:12:56,844 --> 01:12:59,169
Avarice, hanging...

812
01:12:59,263 --> 01:13:00,841
self-destruction.

813
01:13:05,228 --> 01:13:07,434
"I make my own home...

814
01:13:08,523 --> 01:13:10,432
be my gallows."

815
01:13:11,901 --> 01:13:15,068
Thank you, ladies and gentlemen,
for your kind attention.

816
01:13:31,046 --> 01:13:34,164
I'm not a scholar,
but I think you've got the job.

817
01:13:34,256 --> 01:13:35,501
Thank you.

818
01:13:35,591 --> 01:13:38,508
- May I buy you a drink?
- How kind of you. I'd like that.

819
01:13:38,594 --> 01:13:41,511
I'll be a minute
gathering my things.

820
01:13:41,597 --> 01:13:43,590
Take your time.

821
01:13:53,192 --> 01:13:57,356
Allegra, I'll be home
just a little later than I said.

822
01:13:57,446 --> 01:13:59,439
I'm taking Dr Fell out
for a drink.

823
01:14:03,077 --> 01:14:05,200
I can see the people
coming out now.

824
01:14:07,457 --> 01:14:10,126
Yes. Bye, honey. My wife.

825
01:14:10,209 --> 01:14:11,833
Of course.

826
01:14:14,254 --> 01:14:16,924
I should have shown them
this one.

827
01:14:17,007 --> 01:14:20,791
I can't imagine how I missed it.
Remember? I told you about it.

828
01:14:20,886 --> 01:14:23,507
It's a rendering
I found in the Capponi Library.

829
01:14:23,597 --> 01:14:26,349
Can you make it out?

830
01:14:26,433 --> 01:14:29,185
There's a name there...

831
01:14:29,269 --> 01:14:31,345
the one I told you about.

832
01:14:44,368 --> 01:14:46,491
It's your ancestor,
<i>Commendatore...</i>

833
01:14:46,579 --> 01:14:49,151
hanging beneath
these very windows.

834
01:14:49,247 --> 01:14:51,121
Francesco de' Pazzi.

835
01:14:52,375 --> 01:14:55,958
On a related subject,
I must confess to you...

836
01:14:56,046 --> 01:14:58,619
I'm giving very serious thought...

837
01:15:04,721 --> 01:15:06,714
to eating your wife.

838
01:15:40,048 --> 01:15:43,049
If you tell me what I need to know,
<i>Commendatore...</i>

839
01:15:43,134 --> 01:15:45,707
it might be convenient for me
to leave Florence without my meal.

840
01:15:45,803 --> 01:15:49,386
So I'll ask you the questions,
and then we'll see. All right?

841
01:15:49,474 --> 01:15:50,802
Okay?

842
01:16:03,405 --> 01:16:04,650
So.

843
01:16:07,366 --> 01:16:09,774
Now, is it Mason Verger
you sold me to?

844
01:16:11,996 --> 01:16:13,538
No, no.

845
01:16:13,622 --> 01:16:15,829
Blink twice for yes,
once for no.

846
01:16:15,916 --> 01:16:18,454
Was it Mason Verger
you sold me to?

847
01:16:20,087 --> 01:16:21,996
Yes, good. Thank you.

848
01:16:22,089 --> 01:16:25,007
And are his men
waiting for me outside?

849
01:16:26,761 --> 01:16:28,837
Was that a single blink?

850
01:16:28,929 --> 01:16:30,803
You're confused.

851
01:16:30,890 --> 01:16:35,018
Please don't be confused, because I may
have to fillet Signora Pazzi after all.

852
01:16:38,189 --> 01:16:40,645
Have you told anyone
in the <i>questura</i> about me?

853
01:16:42,193 --> 01:16:44,101
No, I thought not.

854
01:16:44,778 --> 01:16:47,814
Have you told Allegra?

855
01:16:50,325 --> 01:16:52,318
No? Are you sure?

856
01:16:54,371 --> 01:16:56,031
I believe you.

857
01:16:58,625 --> 01:17:00,998
Okey-dokey, here we go.

858
01:17:07,551 --> 01:17:08,796
Okay.

859
01:17:10,387 --> 01:17:11,965
Your heart is really palpitating.

860
01:17:12,056 --> 01:17:14,973
Oh, it's not your heart.

861
01:17:16,936 --> 01:17:19,059
Shall I answer it?

862
01:17:21,397 --> 01:17:24,067
<i>I've gone above you.</i>
<i>I've spoken to your section chief.</i>

863
01:17:24,150 --> 01:17:26,902
Someday you'll thank me.
Or you won't. I don't care.

864
01:17:26,986 --> 01:17:29,312
You'll be alive.

865
01:17:29,406 --> 01:17:31,279
Inspector Pazzi?

866
01:17:32,242 --> 01:17:34,531
<i>Is this Clarice?</i>

867
01:17:34,619 --> 01:17:37,075
Hello, Clarice.

868
01:17:38,206 --> 01:17:40,080
I'm afraid I have
bad news for you.

869
01:17:40,166 --> 01:17:43,286
- Is he dead?
- <i>Did you get my note?</i>

870
01:17:43,378 --> 01:17:46,047
<i>I hope you like the skin cream.</i>
<i>I had it specially made for you.</i>

871
01:17:46,131 --> 01:17:48,040
Is he dead, Dr Lecter?

872
01:17:48,133 --> 01:17:52,261
<i>I would love nothing more in this world</i>
<i>than to be able to chat with you.</i>

873
01:17:52,346 --> 01:17:55,512
Unfortunately, you've caught me
at an awkward moment.

874
01:17:55,599 --> 01:17:57,841
Please forgive me.

875
01:17:57,935 --> 01:17:59,677
See you around.

876
01:18:01,938 --> 01:18:03,930
An old friend.

877
01:18:07,944 --> 01:18:09,521
Okay, hold on.

878
01:18:11,239 --> 01:18:12,697
Here we go.

879
01:18:45,022 --> 01:18:49,150
I'll go around back!
Kill him if you have to!

880
01:18:52,363 --> 01:18:54,320
What's it to be?

881
01:18:54,407 --> 01:18:56,565
Bowels in or bowels out...

882
01:18:56,659 --> 01:18:58,651
like judas?

883
01:18:58,744 --> 01:19:00,571
Are you confused?

884
01:19:00,663 --> 01:19:03,498
I'll decide for you,
if you'll permit me.

885
01:20:17,072 --> 01:20:18,352
Good evening.

886
01:21:25,723 --> 01:21:28,261
Cordell...

887
01:21:28,350 --> 01:21:30,260
to you...

888
01:21:30,352 --> 01:21:33,722
does that look
like a wave goodbye...

889
01:21:35,024 --> 01:21:37,432
or hello?

890
01:22:22,613 --> 01:22:25,779
So, what do you think?

891
01:22:25,865 --> 01:22:30,942
Does Lecter want to fuck her
or kill her or eat her or what?

892
01:22:31,037 --> 01:22:33,611
Probably all three.

893
01:22:33,706 --> 01:22:36,328
Though I wouldn't want
to predict in what order.

894
01:22:37,919 --> 01:22:40,492
Here's what I think.

895
01:22:40,588 --> 01:22:44,669
No matter how Barney
might want to romanticize it...

896
01:22:44,759 --> 01:22:48,627
and make it
<i>Beauty and the Beast...</i>

897
01:22:48,722 --> 01:22:51,888
Lecter's object, as I know
from personal experience...

898
01:22:51,975 --> 01:22:54,181
has always been...

899
01:22:54,269 --> 01:22:56,392
degradation...

900
01:22:56,480 --> 01:22:58,721
and suffering.

901
01:22:58,815 --> 01:23:03,560
Get this damn thing off me.
I can't breathe in this thing.

902
01:23:06,155 --> 01:23:09,322
He comes in the guise
of a mentor...

903
01:23:09,408 --> 01:23:12,777
as he did with me and her.

904
01:23:12,870 --> 01:23:16,820
But it's distress that excites him.

905
01:23:16,916 --> 01:23:18,825
To draw him...

906
01:23:20,169 --> 01:23:22,577
she needs to be distressed.

907
01:23:25,383 --> 01:23:29,760
To make her attractive to him,
let him see her distressed.

908
01:23:31,889 --> 01:23:34,463
Let the damage he sees...

909
01:23:34,559 --> 01:23:37,560
suggest the damage
he could do.

910
01:23:46,904 --> 01:23:50,652
When the fox hears the rabbit scream,
he comes a-runnin'.

911
01:23:52,451 --> 01:23:54,444
But not to help.

912
01:23:54,536 --> 01:23:56,446
I don't understand.

913
01:23:56,539 --> 01:23:58,662
<i>There's nothing</i>
<i>to understand, Paul.</i>

914
01:23:58,749 --> 01:24:02,581
<i>All you have to understand</i>
<i>is what it's worth to you.</i>

915
01:24:02,670 --> 01:24:05,587
No, no, I don't understand
why she didn't turn this over.

916
01:24:05,673 --> 01:24:07,630
I mean, she's such
a straight arrow.

917
01:24:07,717 --> 01:24:11,086
She didn't turn it over
because she didn't receive it.

918
01:24:11,178 --> 01:24:13,218
She didn't receive it
because it was never sent.

919
01:24:13,306 --> 01:24:15,713
It was never sent because
Lecter didn't write it.

920
01:24:15,808 --> 01:24:18,381
He didn't write it
because I did.

921
01:24:23,690 --> 01:24:25,599
<i>So, what do you think?</i>

922
01:24:25,692 --> 01:24:29,108
You'd have been better off if
you'd never got her out of trouble.

923
01:24:29,196 --> 01:24:33,193
<i>Oh, woulda, shoulda, coulda. I meant,</i>
<i>what do you think about the money?</i>

924
01:24:33,283 --> 01:24:34,446
Five.

925
01:24:35,535 --> 01:24:39,948
Let's just toss it off, like "five."

926
01:24:40,040 --> 01:24:42,994
Let's say it
with the respect it deserves.

927
01:24:43,085 --> 01:24:46,039
Five hundred thousand dollars.

928
01:24:46,130 --> 01:24:48,003
<i>That's better, but not much.</i>

929
01:24:48,090 --> 01:24:50,497
- Now, will it work?
- <i>It'll work.</i>

930
01:24:50,592 --> 01:24:52,715
It won't be pretty.

931
01:24:52,803 --> 01:24:54,796
<i>What ever is?</i>

932
01:24:58,266 --> 01:25:00,424
Cocksucker.

933
01:25:00,518 --> 01:25:03,472
Never seen this before
in my life.

934
01:25:03,563 --> 01:25:07,940
Then how do you account for its being
found in your office, your basement?

935
01:25:08,026 --> 01:25:10,943
How do you want me to answer that,
Mr Krendler?

936
01:25:11,029 --> 01:25:13,946
What possible reason
might I have to withhold it?

937
01:25:14,032 --> 01:25:17,282
Perhaps because of the nature
of its content.

938
01:25:17,369 --> 01:25:20,323
Reads to me like a love letter.

939
01:25:20,413 --> 01:25:23,498
- Has it been tested for prints?
- No prints on it. None on the last one.

940
01:25:23,583 --> 01:25:25,457
Handwriting analysis?

941
01:25:25,544 --> 01:25:29,162
"Did you ever think, Clarice, why
the philistines don't understand you?

942
01:25:29,256 --> 01:25:31,544
It's because you're the answer
to Samson's riddle.

943
01:25:31,633 --> 01:25:33,708
You are the honey in the lion."

944
01:25:33,801 --> 01:25:35,295
Sounds like him to me.

945
01:25:35,386 --> 01:25:39,680
- Do you mean, like a homosexual?
- Like a nut with a crush.

946
01:25:39,765 --> 01:25:41,094
Director Noonan,
I need to say something...

947
01:25:41,183 --> 01:25:43,674
Agent Starling, I am placing you
on administrative leave...

948
01:25:43,769 --> 01:25:47,933
till document analysis tells me
unequivocally a mistake's been made.

949
01:25:48,024 --> 01:25:51,227
In the meantime, you remain eligible
for insurance and medical benefits.

950
01:25:51,319 --> 01:25:54,403
Surrender your weapons and
your identification to Agent Pearsall.

951
01:26:07,335 --> 01:26:10,087
I want to say something.
I think I'm entitled.

952
01:26:10,171 --> 01:26:11,914
Go ahead.

953
01:26:12,005 --> 01:26:15,457
I think Mr Mason Verger is
trying to capture Dr Lecter...

954
01:26:15,551 --> 01:26:17,543
for the purposes
of personal revenge.

955
01:26:17,636 --> 01:26:20,127
I think Mr Krendler
is in collusion with him...

956
01:26:20,222 --> 01:26:23,140
and wants the FBI's efforts against
Dr Lecter to work for Mr Verger.

957
01:26:23,225 --> 01:26:26,096
I think Mr Krendler
is being paid to do this.

958
01:26:26,186 --> 01:26:29,887
- Lucky you're not sworn here today.
- Swear me! You swear too!

959
01:26:29,982 --> 01:26:32,734
Clarice,
if the evidence is lacking...

960
01:26:32,818 --> 01:26:35,440
you'll be entitled to full reinstatement
without prejudice...

961
01:26:35,529 --> 01:26:39,942
if you don't do or say
anything in the meantime...

962
01:26:40,034 --> 01:26:42,572
that would make that impossible.

963
01:26:43,037 --> 01:26:46,073
<i>Relieved of field duty pending</i>
<i>an internal investigation...</i>

964
01:26:46,165 --> 01:26:49,119
<i>Special Agent Clarice Starling,</i>
<i>a ten-year veteran on the Bureau...</i>

965
01:26:49,209 --> 01:26:51,248
<i>began her career</i>
<i>with an assignment...</i>

966
01:26:51,336 --> 01:26:53,412
<i>to interview lethal madman</i>
<i>Hannibal Lecter.</i>

967
01:26:53,505 --> 01:26:57,337
<i>Earlier, we heard comments from Justice</i>
<i>Department spokesman Paul Krendler.</i>

968
01:26:58,468 --> 01:27:01,718
<i>Can you comment on theJustice</i>
<i>Department's decision this morning?</i>

969
01:27:01,805 --> 01:27:05,885
<i>The FBI and theJustice Department are</i>
<i>looking very carefully into the charges.</i>

970
01:27:05,976 --> 01:27:08,301
<i>And, yes, they are extremely serious.</i>

971
01:27:08,395 --> 01:27:09,889
<i>I'd like to add</i>
<i>a personal note, though.</i>

972
01:27:09,980 --> 01:27:14,606
<i>- Starling's one of our best agents.</i>
- No, no, no, stay.

973
01:27:14,693 --> 01:27:18,691
<i>I would be very surprised if these</i>
<i>accusations turn out to be true.</i>

974
01:27:18,780 --> 01:27:22,232
<i>Is theJustice Department and FBI</i>
<i>united in this decision?</i>

975
01:27:22,326 --> 01:27:25,031
<i>It's much too soon to condemn her...</i>

976
01:28:10,289 --> 01:28:11,997
Good boy.

977
01:30:54,201 --> 01:30:56,574
<i>I think she's nice.</i>

978
01:30:56,662 --> 01:30:59,533
<i>She's always been nice to me.</i>
<i>Polite.</i>

979
01:30:59,624 --> 01:31:01,118
<i>Don't you think?</i>

980
01:31:01,209 --> 01:31:04,126
<i>Do you know what</i>
<i>a roller pigeon is, Barney?</i>

981
01:31:04,212 --> 01:31:06,537
<i>Roller pigeons</i>
<i>climb high and fast...</i>

982
01:31:06,631 --> 01:31:09,715
<i>then roll over and fall</i>
<i>Just as fast towards the Earth.</i>

983
01:31:09,801 --> 01:31:13,134
<i>There are shallow rollers</i>
<i>and there are deep rollers...</i>

984
01:31:13,221 --> 01:31:16,636
<i>but you can't breed two deep rollers,</i>
<i>or their young, their offspring...</i>

985
01:31:16,723 --> 01:31:20,139
<i>will roll all the way down,</i>
<i>hit and die.</i>

986
01:31:20,227 --> 01:31:24,225
<i>Agent Starling is a deep roller.</i>

987
01:31:24,314 --> 01:31:27,232
<i>Let's hope</i>
<i>one of her parents was not.</i>

988
01:32:57,490 --> 01:32:59,898
<i>The power in that battery</i>
<i>is low, Clarice.</i>

989
01:32:59,993 --> 01:33:02,698
<i>I would've changed it,</i>
<i>but I didn't want to wake you.</i>

990
01:33:02,787 --> 01:33:07,117
<i>Use the one in the charger. Hopefully,</i>
<i>the light on it is green by now.</i>

991
01:33:07,208 --> 01:33:09,912
<i>Because this is gonna be a long call</i>
<i>and I can't let you off...</i>

992
01:33:10,002 --> 01:33:12,410
<i>because even though</i>
<i>you've been stripped of your duties...</i>

993
01:33:12,505 --> 01:33:15,790
<i>I know you won't abandon them...</i>
<i>you'll try to put on a trace.</i>

994
01:33:15,883 --> 01:33:19,501
<i>So we'll disconnect long enough for you</i>
<i>to exchange the battery in the phone...</i>

995
01:33:19,595 --> 01:33:21,588
<i>for the one in the charger.</i>

996
01:33:21,681 --> 01:33:24,681
<i>Shall we say, three seconds?</i>

997
01:33:24,767 --> 01:33:26,309
<i>- Are you ready?</i>
- Yes.

998
01:33:26,394 --> 01:33:27,343
<i>Go.</i>

999
01:33:32,900 --> 01:33:34,774
- <i>Very good.</i>
- Thank you.

1000
01:33:34,861 --> 01:33:37,778
<i>Remember, Clarice, if you get caught</i>
<i>with a concealed, unlicensed firearm...</i>

1001
01:33:37,864 --> 01:33:40,699
<i>in the District of Columbia,</i>
<i>the penalty is very stiff.</i>

1002
01:33:40,783 --> 01:33:44,366
<i>But bring the guns if you have to.</i>
<i>Now get in your car.</i>

1003
01:34:21,365 --> 01:34:23,607
<i>The reason we're doing it</i>
<i>like this, Clarice...</i>

1004
01:34:23,701 --> 01:34:27,745
<i>is because I like to watch you</i>
<i>as we speak, with your eyes open.</i>

1005
01:34:28,955 --> 01:34:32,573
<i>No, it does not excite me.</i>
<i>It pleases me.</i>

1006
01:34:32,667 --> 01:34:35,075
<i>You have very shapely feet.</i>

1007
01:34:38,256 --> 01:34:40,830
<i>Where are we now?</i>
<i>Call it out.</i>

1008
01:34:40,926 --> 01:34:42,717
Massachusetts Avenue.

1009
01:34:42,803 --> 01:34:44,676
<i>Take it.</i>

1010
01:34:44,763 --> 01:34:48,547
<i>I thought, to begin with,</i>
<i>you might tell me how you're feeling.</i>

1011
01:34:48,642 --> 01:34:49,591
About what?

1012
01:34:49,685 --> 01:34:52,555
<i>The masters you serve</i>
<i>and how they've treated you.</i>

1013
01:34:52,646 --> 01:34:55,351
<i>Your career, such as it is.</i>

1014
01:34:55,440 --> 01:34:57,314
<i>Your life, Clarice.</i>

1015
01:34:57,401 --> 01:34:59,358
I thought we might
talk about yours.

1016
01:34:59,444 --> 01:35:02,444
<i>- What's the next cross street?</i>
- Capitol Street.

1017
01:35:02,530 --> 01:35:06,777
<i>In two blocks, make a left</i>
<i>into Union Station. Park.</i>

1018
01:35:08,077 --> 01:35:10,485
<i>My life? What is there</i>
<i>to say about mine?</i>

1019
01:35:10,580 --> 01:35:13,664
I have been in a state of hibernation
for some time...

1020
01:35:13,750 --> 01:35:15,826
<i>a little inactive.</i>

1021
01:35:15,918 --> 01:35:19,204
<i>But now I'm back home</i>
<i>and I'm very happy...</i>

1022
01:35:19,297 --> 01:35:21,005
<i>and very healthy.</i>

1023
01:35:21,090 --> 01:35:25,468
<i>- You. It's you I'm worried about.</i>
- I'm fine.

1024
01:35:25,553 --> 01:35:28,340
<i>No, you're certainly</i>
<i>not fine, Clarice.</i>

1025
01:35:28,431 --> 01:35:31,136
<i>You fell in love with the Bureau,</i>
<i>the institution...</i>

1026
01:35:31,226 --> 01:35:34,595
<i>only to discover, after giving it</i>
<i>everything you've got...</i>

1027
01:35:34,688 --> 01:35:36,764
that it does not
love you back...

1028
01:35:36,856 --> 01:35:38,849
that, in fact, it resents you.

1029
01:35:38,942 --> 01:35:41,895
It resents you more than the husband
and children you gave up to it.

1030
01:35:41,986 --> 01:35:46,446
<i>Why is that, do you think?</i>
<i>Why are you so resented?</i>

1031
01:35:46,532 --> 01:35:48,987
- Tell me.
- Tell you?

1032
01:35:49,076 --> 01:35:50,701
God bless you.

1033
01:35:50,786 --> 01:35:52,660
Well, isn't it clear?

1034
01:35:54,415 --> 01:35:57,831
You serve the idea
of order, Clarice.

1035
01:35:57,918 --> 01:35:59,294
<i>They don't.</i>

1036
01:35:59,378 --> 01:36:02,961
<i>You believe in the oath you took.</i>
<i>They don't.</i>

1037
01:36:03,049 --> 01:36:07,426
<i>You feel it is your duty</i>
<i>to protect the sheep. They don't.</i>

1038
01:36:07,512 --> 01:36:09,634
<i>They don't like you</i>
<i>because you're not like them.</i>

1039
01:36:09,722 --> 01:36:11,928
<i>They hate you and envy you.</i>

1040
01:36:12,016 --> 01:36:15,765
<i>They are weak, unruly</i>
<i>and believe in nothing.</i>

1041
01:36:15,853 --> 01:36:18,390
Mason Verger wants to kill you,
Dr Lecter.

1042
01:36:18,480 --> 01:36:21,232
Turn yourself in to me,
and I promise no one will hurt you.

1043
01:36:21,316 --> 01:36:24,851
<i>Will you stay with me in my prison cell</i>
<i>and hold my hand, Clarice?</i>

1044
01:36:24,945 --> 01:36:27,270
<i>We could have some fun.</i>

1045
01:36:27,364 --> 01:36:30,815
<i>No, Mason Verger does not want to kill</i>
<i>me any more than I want to kill him.</i>

1046
01:36:30,909 --> 01:36:34,824
<i>Hejust wants to see me suffer</i>
<i>in some unimaginable way.</i>

1047
01:36:34,913 --> 01:36:37,036
<i>He is rather twisted,</i>
<i>you know.</i>

1048
01:36:37,124 --> 01:36:39,580
Have you had the pleasure
of meeting him?

1049
01:36:39,668 --> 01:36:41,875
Face-to-face, so to speak?

1050
01:36:41,962 --> 01:36:43,871
Yes.

1051
01:36:43,964 --> 01:36:47,084
<i>- Attractive, isn't he?</i>
- Dr Lecter?

1052
01:36:51,555 --> 01:36:53,548
<i>Okay, back to you.</i>

1053
01:36:53,641 --> 01:36:55,882
I want to know what it is
you think you will do...

1054
01:36:55,975 --> 01:36:59,309
now that everything you've ever cared
about has been taken away from you.

1055
01:36:59,396 --> 01:37:01,803
I don't know, Dr Lecter.

1056
01:37:01,898 --> 01:37:04,733
<i>Clarice, do you think you'll work</i>
<i>as a chambermaid...</i>

1057
01:37:04,818 --> 01:37:07,569
<i>at a motel on Route 66...</i>

1058
01:37:07,654 --> 01:37:10,359
<i>Just like your mommy?</i>

1059
01:37:19,624 --> 01:37:21,700
<i>What are you thinking now?</i>

1060
01:37:21,793 --> 01:37:25,838
Are you paying attention to me,
ex-Special Agent Starling?

1061
01:37:26,673 --> 01:37:30,007
<i>Are you, by any chance,</i>
<i>trying to trace my whereabouts?</i>

1062
01:37:34,055 --> 01:37:37,506
- I'm being followed, Dr Lecter.
- <i>I know. I've seen them.</i>

1063
01:37:37,600 --> 01:37:40,471
<i>And now you're in</i>
<i>a real dilemma, aren't you?</i>

1064
01:37:40,561 --> 01:37:44,393
<i>Do you continue to try to find me,</i>
<i>knowing that you are leading them to me?</i>

1065
01:37:44,482 --> 01:37:48,100
<i>Do you have so much faith in your</i>
<i>abilities that you honestly believe...</i>

1066
01:37:48,194 --> 01:37:52,026
<i>you can somehow simultaneously</i>
<i>arrest me and them?</i>

1067
01:37:52,115 --> 01:37:56,065
<i>It could get very messy, Clarice,</i>
<i>like the fish market.</i>

1068
01:37:57,787 --> 01:38:00,456
- <i>What if I did it for you?</i>
- Did what?

1069
01:38:00,540 --> 01:38:04,075
<i>Harmed them, Clarice,</i>
<i>the ones who have harmed you.</i>

1070
01:38:04,169 --> 01:38:07,454
<i>What if I made them</i>
<i>scream apologies?</i>

1071
01:38:07,547 --> 01:38:09,540
<i>No, I shouldn't even say it...</i>

1072
01:38:09,632 --> 01:38:13,001
<i>because you'll feel, with your</i>
<i>perfect grasp of right and wrong...</i>

1073
01:38:13,093 --> 01:38:15,335
<i>that you were somehow</i> accompli.

1074
01:38:16,639 --> 01:38:18,133
Don't help me.

1075
01:38:19,642 --> 01:38:21,634
No, of course not.
Forget I said it.

1076
01:38:26,607 --> 01:38:29,394
<i>Clarice, you were very,</i>
<i>very warm.</i>

1077
01:38:29,485 --> 01:38:31,478
<i>You were so close.</i>

1078
01:38:35,700 --> 01:38:38,617
<i>And now you're getting</i>
<i>colder again.</i>

1079
01:38:38,703 --> 01:38:40,909
<i>Yeah, warmer again.</i>

1080
01:38:40,997 --> 01:38:45,160
<i>Well, I think I've been generous</i>
<i>enough with you and the clues.</i>

1081
01:38:45,251 --> 01:38:48,750
<i>- You're on your own now, Clarice.</i>
- Dr Lecter.

1082
01:38:58,013 --> 01:39:00,765
<i>Hope you like them, Clarice.</i>
<i>Ta-ta.</i>

1083
01:39:30,670 --> 01:39:32,248
Go.

1084
01:39:48,772 --> 01:39:50,681
Get out of the way!

1085
01:40:02,285 --> 01:40:05,120
I know the first thing a hysteric
says is, "I am not a hysteric"...

1086
01:40:05,204 --> 01:40:08,490
but I am not a hysteric.
I am calm.

1087
01:40:08,583 --> 01:40:11,453
I'll ask you one time.
Think before you answer.

1088
01:40:12,712 --> 01:40:15,666
Think about every good thing
you ever did.

1089
01:40:15,756 --> 01:40:17,630
Think about what you swore.

1090
01:40:17,717 --> 01:40:21,002
Two men in a van,
a third driving, another man down.

1091
01:40:21,095 --> 01:40:23,633
They put him in the back.
I think it was Lecter.

1092
01:40:23,723 --> 01:40:27,092
I gave you a licence, and I'm reporting
it to you again in front of witnesses.

1093
01:40:29,145 --> 01:40:30,770
All right.

1094
01:40:31,898 --> 01:40:33,891
I'll go with it as a kidnapping.

1095
01:40:34,567 --> 01:40:36,643
I'll send someone
with the local authorities...

1096
01:40:36,736 --> 01:40:39,025
if they'll let us on the property
without a warrant.

1097
01:40:39,114 --> 01:40:43,442
- I should go. You could deputize me.
- No. You're not going.

1098
01:40:43,534 --> 01:40:46,203
You're going home,
where you'll wait for me to call...

1099
01:40:46,286 --> 01:40:49,987
and tell you what,
if anything, we've found.

1100
01:40:51,292 --> 01:40:54,577
Thank Mr Verger for letting us look
around. Sorry if we inconvenienced him.

1101
01:40:54,670 --> 01:40:56,746
He's always happy to see you.

1102
01:41:06,349 --> 01:41:08,388
Phone.

1103
01:41:08,476 --> 01:41:11,049
<i>What number, please?</i>

1104
01:41:11,145 --> 01:41:12,520
Carlo.

1105
01:41:20,321 --> 01:41:21,898
Give me one.

1106
01:41:26,493 --> 01:41:28,949
- <i>How is he?</i>
- Sleeping.

1107
01:41:29,037 --> 01:41:31,789
Bring him home.

1108
01:41:54,855 --> 01:41:58,306
<i>You've reached Clarice Starling.</i>
<i>Please leave a message.</i>

1109
01:41:58,400 --> 01:41:59,942
<i>Pick up, Starling.</i>

1110
01:42:00,026 --> 01:42:01,983
<i>There was nothing out there.</i>

1111
01:42:02,070 --> 01:42:04,477
<i>I'm gonna say it again,</i>
<i>in case you didn't hear me.</i>

1112
01:42:04,572 --> 01:42:08,487
<i>You are not a law officer while</i>
<i>you're on suspension. You'reJoe Blow.</i>

1113
01:42:09,661 --> 01:42:12,662
<i>Hope for your sake</i>
<i>you're in the bathroom.</i>

1114
01:42:51,828 --> 01:42:53,452
<i>Hylochoerus...</i>

1115
01:42:53,538 --> 01:42:56,704
<i>meinertzhageni.</i>

1116
01:42:56,791 --> 01:43:00,871
Ring any bells from
high school biology, Doctor?

1117
01:43:01,963 --> 01:43:03,872
No?

1118
01:43:03,965 --> 01:43:07,548
Well, I could list
its most conspicuous features...

1119
01:43:07,635 --> 01:43:10,387
if that would help
jog the memory.

1120
01:43:11,139 --> 01:43:14,056
Three pairs of incisors...

1121
01:43:14,142 --> 01:43:18,719
one pair of elongated canines...

1122
01:43:20,230 --> 01:43:23,564
three pairs of molars...

1123
01:43:23,651 --> 01:43:26,189
four pairs of premolars...

1124
01:43:26,278 --> 01:43:28,567
upper and lower...

1125
01:43:28,656 --> 01:43:33,567
for a total of <i>44</i> teeth.

1126
01:43:38,374 --> 01:43:43,250
The meal will begin with
an hors d'oeuvres tartare...

1127
01:43:44,714 --> 01:43:47,418
your feet.

1128
01:43:47,508 --> 01:43:49,501
The main course...
the rest of you...

